[{"type":"paragraph text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":1,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“At that time,” says Yahweh, “they will bring the bones of the kings of Judah, the bones of his princes, the bones of the priests, the bones of the prophets, and the bones of the inhabitants of Jerusalem, out of their graves.  "},{"type":"paragraph text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":2,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"They will spread them before the sun, the moon, and all the army of the sky, which they have loved, which they have served, after which they have walked, which they have sought, and which they have worshiped. They will not be gathered or be buried. They will be like dung on the surface of the earth.  "},{"type":"paragraph text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":3,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Death will be chosen rather than life by all the residue that remain of this evil family, that remain in all the places where I have driven them,” says Yahweh of Armies.  "},{"type":"paragraph text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“Moreover you shall tell them, ‘Yahweh says: "},{"type":"paragraph end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"“ ‘Do men fall, and not rise up again? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Does one turn away, and not return? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":5,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Why then have the people of Jerusalem fallen back by a perpetual backsliding? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":5,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"They cling to deceit. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":5,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"They refuse to return. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"I listened and heard, but they didn’t say what is right. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"No one repents of his wickedness, saying, “What have I done?” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Everyone turns to his course, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"as a horse that rushes headlong in the battle. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":7,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Yes, the stork in the sky knows her appointed times. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":7,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"The turtledove, the swallow, and the crane observe the time of their coming; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":7,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"but my people don’t know Yahweh’s law. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":7,"sectionNumber":4,"value":" "},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":8,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“ ‘How do you say, “We are wise, and Yahweh’s law is with us?” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":8,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"But, behold, the false pen of the scribes has made that a lie. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":9,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"The wise men are disappointed. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":9,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"They are dismayed and trapped. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":9,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Behold, they have rejected Yahweh’s word. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":9,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"What kind of wisdom is in them? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":10,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Therefore I will give their wives to others "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":10,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"and their fields to those who will possess them. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":10,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"For everyone from the least even to the greatest is given to covetousness; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":10,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"from the prophet even to the priest everyone deals falsely. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":11,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"They have healed the hurt of the daughter of my people slightly, saying, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":11,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"“Peace, peace,” when there is no peace. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Were they ashamed when they had committed abomination? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"No, they were not at all ashamed. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"They couldn’t blush. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"Therefore they will fall among those who fall. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"In the time of their visitation they will be cast down, says Yahweh. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":6,"value":" "},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“ ‘I will utterly consume them, says Yahweh. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"No grapes will be on the vine, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"no figs on the fig tree, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"and the leaf will fade. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"The things that I have given them "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":6,"value":"will pass away from them.’ ” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":7,"value":" "},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":14,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“Why do we sit still? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":14,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"Assemble yourselves! "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":14,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Let’s enter into the fortified cities, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":14,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"and let’s be silent there; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":14,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"for Yahweh our God has put us to silence, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":14,"sectionNumber":6,"value":"and given us poisoned water to drink, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":14,"sectionNumber":7,"value":"because we have sinned against Yahweh. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":15,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"We looked for peace, but no good came; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":15,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"and for a time of healing, and behold, dismay! "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":16,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"The snorting of his horses is heard from Dan. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":16,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"The whole land trembles at the sound of the neighing of his strong ones; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":16,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"for they have come, and have devoured the land and all that is in it, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":16,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"the city and those who dwell therein.” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":17,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“For, behold, I will send serpents, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":17,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"adders among you, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":17,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"which will not be charmed; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":17,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"and they will bite you,” says Yahweh. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":18,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Oh that I could comfort myself against sorrow! "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":18,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"My heart is faint within me. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":19,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Behold, the voice of the cry of the daughter of my people from a land that is very far off: "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":19,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"“Isn’t Yahweh in Zion? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":19,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Isn’t her King in her?” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":19,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"“Why have they provoked me to anger with their engraved images, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":19,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"and with foreign idols?” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":19,"sectionNumber":6,"value":" "},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":20,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“The harvest is past. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":20,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"The summer has ended, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":20,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"and we are not saved.” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":20,"sectionNumber":4,"value":" "},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":21,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"For the hurt of the daughter of my people, I am hurt. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":21,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"I mourn. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":21,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Dismay has taken hold of me. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":22,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Is there no balm in Gilead? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":22,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"Is there no physician there? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":8,"verseNumber":22,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Why then isn’t the health of the daughter of my people recovered? "},{"type":"line break"}]